name: The Web Picture Experience in 1996
description: Macintosh Performa or Pentium 100MHz PC. 800x600px display. Netscape Navigator. Dial-up connection with a 14400 modem. Get the picture? For anyone not born in 1978 or earlier, the present oeuvre seeks to replicate the user experience in those times. As you may know, early advances in Internet tech were always spurred by the adult business. Websites with image galleries? Embedded video in HTML? Live webcams? Faster connection? You know for what all of these are useful. File specs: animated GIF, 4
